Observables represent a stream of data/events that will arrive over time. We combine observables and operatives to create a pipeline of transformations that a stream of data flow through.
export class TestComponent implements OnInit{
  constructor(private route: ActivatedRoute) { }

  ngOnInit(): void {
    this.route.data.subscribe((data) => {
      console.log(data);
    });

}

In the above code, the subscribe method is an observer. The code block
route.data

is the observable sending the data to the
